	<div class="About Us" id="AboutUs">
	<h2>About Us</h2>
		Institute Of Musculoskeletal Disorders and Orthopaedics in the City Hospital is comprised 
		of a multidisciplinary team of orthopaedic surgeons, anaesthesia and pain medicine 
		specialists and physical and occupational therapists. 
		 Our specialists are focused on all musculoskeletal conditions including joint pain, 
		 spine pain, trauma, sports, birth and congenital defects and other injuries. 
		 The Institute is equipped with the latest technologies such as Computer Navigation Systems,
		  O-Arm, 
		Alpha Operation Theatre, Arthroscopic Equipment, 4D Myoline Dynamic Posture and
		 Motion Analysis.
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="What we Treat" id="WhatweTreat?">
	<h2>What we Treat?</h2>
		At Institute Of Musculoskeletal Disorders and Orthopaedics, the doctors, nurses and
		therapists work in coordination to provide quality services to patients suffering from 
		disorders of the musculoskeletal system.
		<br>
		<ul type="square">
		<li>Spinal Tumour
		<li>Degenerative disc diseases
		<li>Trauma Injuries
		<li>Congenital limb deformities
		<li>Bone Tumours
		<li>Brachial plexus injuries
		<li>Arthritis
		<li>Scoliosis
		<li>Sports Injuries
		<li>Spinal Deformities
		</ul>
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="How we Treat" id="HowweTreat?">
	<h2>How we Treat?</h2>
	Combining research and academics with the latest technology for patient treatment,
	the Institute Of Musculoskeletal Disorders and Orthopaedics, aims at reducing the toll 
	of orthopaedic disorders across age groups. The team of doctors and surgeons at the Institute
	 are supported by trained nurses, experienced physiotherapists and occupational therapists 
	 who provide pre- and post-operative treatment on out-patient, in-patient, and domiciliary basis.
	</div>
